Text.Value: I often am. Farewell.
To fix a mistake. I didn't mean to kill you.
What the... it's gone! The artefact - what have you done with it?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Looks down at herself, realising box is missing. Looks up to player.

Text.Value: What now?
No - you're trying to trick me. You must have it. I'll take it off your corpse soon enough.

EditorData.NodeContext: Suspicious, angry. Convinced the player has the object she's supposed to protect. Combat rigth afterwards

Text.Value: Fine. But don't delay.
I wanted to kill you myself.
Well, make sure it's a mistake you don't repeat. I've enough problems with my memory as it is...
I had so much fun killing you last time, I figured I'd do it again.
You know, I think I'd rather take my chances without you.
Wait - you're the one who attacked me! What the hells are you playing at?!

EditorData.NodeContext: Surprised and angry (player knocked her unconscious, now revived her)

Text.Value: Lead the way.
I intend to, trust me... On that score, maybe we should stay together - better odds of survival.
I'll join - if I can speak to whoever's really in charge. Otherwise, I'd best be on my way.
Perhaps we'll meet again. If you survive, that is.
I'll mark my camp on your map. You can rest there.
Wait. Perhaps we shouldn't. You're not the one I need to talk to, are you? Not really.

EditorData.NodeContext: realisation that she isn't talking to the person in charge.

Text.Value: Your memory? What's wrong?
I can feel it, in your head. You follow someone else's orders. I'll deal with them, not you.
Yes. But it'll soon be remedied, once I've taken what's mine from your corpse.

EditorData.NodeContext: Suspicious, angry. Convinced the player has the object she's supposed to protect. Combat rigth afterwards

Text.Value: Bloody maniac!
You're on your own.
What the - you're the one who killed me! Why did you bring me back?

EditorData.NodeContext: Surprised and alarmed (the player killed her, then resurrected her)

Text.Value: Now, instead of killing and resurrecting each other, we should just work together and try to stay alive.
None of your concern - it's mine now.
I can't let you do that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Steely resolve - she's going to fight the player to get the box back.

Text.Value: Artefact? I don't have anything like that.
We've got the same problem, after all. Let's try to find a solution together, before it's too late.
Thank you... maybe I should come with you - return the favour by watching your back.
Fine. I'll see about introducing you.
Nothing. You and I ought to be considering how we're going to survive this mess - we should stay together.
Seems you're the closest thing to an ally I've encountered so far - we should stay together, in the interest of survival.
Thank you... though you shouldn't have had it to begin with.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Fallback just in case SH is in party (shouldn't be possible)
EditorData.NodeContext: Grateful, but with a dash of suspicion.

Text.Value: All right, fine. Let's stay together.
How gracious of you. Try it again, and I'll leave you in pieces.
Take what? You don't have it!
*Your mind briefly swaps with hers. You both wince in discomfort as you recognise you share the same infection.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: SH and the player briedly recoil from the effects of the mindmeld.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Mindmeld narration node only if SH wasn't met previously

Text.Value: You seem overburdened with hangers-on already.
Leave.
I decided you might prove useful.
Wait - after all that, you won't join me?
Here, take it.
I did. You're welcome.
It was a mistake - I didn't mean to knock you out.

EditorData.logicalname: SH KNOCKED OUT AND HELPED UP

Text.Value: I can't promise I'll wait forever. Perhaps our paths will cross again later.
There must be some kind of mistake.
I'm alive... did you save me?
Just try to stay alive this time.
Well make sure it's a mistake you don't repeat.
That said, you're the likeliest ally I've encountered so far. Perhaps we should stay together.

Synopsis: The player resurrects or revives Shadowheart after she was killed or knocked unconscious. Shadowheart can recognise the player as her attacker if that is the case, and reacts to the loss of her box if it was taken from her.
